## 6. Authentication & authorization

- **Sessions** — cookie-based, signed cookie holds a `Session.id`. Stored in the DB so
  sessions can be terminated server-side. Every request is gated by
  `Authentication#require_authentication` unless the controller opts out with
  `allow_unauthenticated_access`.
- **Role gating** — the three role-namespaced base controllers
  (`Members::BaseController`, `FactCheckers::BaseController`, `Admins::BaseController`)
  enforce the role check via `before_action`. Hitting an admin URL as a member redirects
  to root.
- **Authorization** — Pundit is wired in (`include Pundit::Authorization`). Currently
  only `ClaimPolicy` is in active use; most authorization happens via the role gates
  above and scope filtering inside controllers (e.g. fact-checker assignments are
  always scoped to `current_fact_checker.assignments`).
- **Password reset** — `User.generates_token_for(:password_reset)` creates a 15-minute
  signed token bound to the password salt, so changing the password invalidates any
  outstanding tokens. Reset flow lives in `PasswordsController`. Request always returns
  the same generic notice regardless of whether the email exists, to avoid leaking
  account existence.

